parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
electrical circuit shorts drain the battery continuously
the transmission overheating light comes on
the air conditioning stops working
the brakes make a different sound
the airbag warning indicator illuminates
and the windshield wipers fail to activate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Control Unit (ECU) or Power Supply Unit (PSU) can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the transmission overheating light comes on
the air conditioning stops working
the airbag warning indicator illuminates
and the windshield wipers fail to activate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lighting system can cause reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents or make it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The tail lights and tag lights do not work
the dashboard indicator for the headlight shows the parking light symbol for both parking lights and headlights
and the headlights do not turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion issues can cause electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start due to corrosion issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Timing Belt Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, it can result in costly repairs, financial losses, and inconvenience to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the engine makes unusual noises
the timing belt snaps
the engine compression levels are low
the engine may be difficult or impossible to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Replacement Parts for Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for recall repairs can lead to extended periods of time where the vehicle is not safe to operate, putting the driver and others at risk. It can also cause inconvenience, financial losses, and frustration for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives a recall notification
but the necessary parts are unavailable
the vehicle owner is unable to schedule a repair
the vehicle owner is forced to continue driving a potentially dangerous vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents or injuries. It can also result in costly repairs, financial losses, and inconvenience to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the oil level drops rapidly
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine may be difficult or impossible to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shutting off can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic. It can also result in costly repairs, financial losses, and inconvenience to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the engine makes unusual noises
the vehicle may be difficult or impossible to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Cradle and Control Arm Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cradle and control arm can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the check engine
4-WD
ABS
traction control
and oil pressure warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the muffler can cause loud noises and potentially lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: A loud noise is heard coming from the vehicle
the muffler is detached.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive belt system can cause engine damage and lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive belt system fails
the vehicle is unable to be repaired due to unavailable parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine and Engine Cooling System Failure

symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
